WEBVTT

00:02.735 --> 00:04.213
I wasn't even expecting you.

00:04.237 --> 00:05.840
How come you didn't
use your own keys?

00:05.864 --> 00:07.341
Were you waiting out there long?

00:07.365 --> 00:08.926
No, not very.

00:08.950 --> 00:10.845
So anyway, we're
just sitting there

00:10.869 --> 00:14.339
and he just walks in, like,
"Hello, I'm your grandfather."

00:14.831 --> 00:17.393
And nobody knew what
to say, you know?

00:17.417 --> 00:20.354
And I don't... I don't really
know what it means, that he...

00:20.378 --> 00:21.888
that he showed up.

00:22.047 --> 00:23.357
I mean, maybe...

00:23.381 --> 00:25.610
Maybe I guilted him into
wanting to meet them.

00:25.634 --> 00:28.728
But, then... Then,
can we trust him?

00:29.012 --> 00:30.323
You know, is he
gonna stick around?

00:30.347 --> 00:33.524
The guy's definitely got a history of
flaking out on people, that's for sure.

00:33.934 --> 00:37.570
- Take off your jacket.
- I wasn't planning on staying.

00:38.647 --> 00:40.198
Apparently, neither are you.

00:40.440 --> 00:41.417
What?

00:41.441 --> 00:44.420
Well, I ran into Warren
Danziger at the coffeehouse.

00:44.444 --> 00:45.713
He had a message for you.

00:45.737 --> 00:47.590
He said that he got into
Hampshire State, too,

00:47.614 --> 00:49.415
and if you were looking
for a roommate...

00:49.699 --> 00:52.053
And I said, "What are
you talking about?

00:52.077 --> 00:53.930
You know, Bailey's not going
back East for school.

00:53.954 --> 00:55.514
He's staying here
in San Francisco."

00:55.538 --> 00:58.174
But apparently that's not what
your guidance counselor told him.

00:59.501 --> 01:01.219
Okay.

01:02.420 --> 01:03.972
Okay, look. First of all...

01:04.339 --> 01:06.442
First of all, when I applied
to Hampshire State,

01:06.466 --> 01:10.029
you and I, we weren't even...
we weren't even together yet.

01:10.053 --> 01:12.698
And I never thought that I
would get into that place.

01:12.722 --> 01:15.942
It was, like, this huge long shot.
Really.

01:16.226 --> 01:18.528
Okay. Yes.

01:19.062 --> 01:20.863
Yes, I got accepted.

01:21.856 --> 01:23.574
But you're not gonna go, right?

01:25.235 --> 01:27.755
- Well...
- God.

01:27.779 --> 01:31.175
Sarah, listen, before
you get upset,

01:31.199 --> 01:33.177
I-I know what you're
thinking, and...

01:33.201 --> 01:35.179
And you have to know that
me going away to college

01:35.203 --> 01:36.972
isn't gonna change anything
between us at all.

01:36.996 --> 01:38.683
What are you talking
about, Bailey?

01:38.707 --> 01:40.893
You're leaving. You're
going 3000 miles away.

01:40.917 --> 01:42.728
You're going as far away
from here as you can get.

01:42.752 --> 01:44.313
- That changes everything.
- Sarah, listen...

01:44.337 --> 01:47.306
You're someone to be
talking about flaking out.

